Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour enough oil into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop into the oven. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{700%g} into 4cm chunks. Boil the potatoes for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

Meanwhile, peel and coarsely grate the @parsnip{1}. Roughly chop the @pecan nut halves{40}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Trim and halve the @Chantenay carrots{225%g} lengthways (no need to peel), then pop them onto a large baking tray and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

When ready, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} and sprinkle on the @plain flour for the potatoes{1%tsp}. Shake to fluff them up, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray, gently turning in the oil.

Season the potatoes with @salt{}, then roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{45-50%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium saucepan on high heat. Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once browned, lower the heat slightly. Add the grated parsnip and a knob of @butter{30%g} (if you have any). Fry until the parsnip has softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Stir in the lentils, pecans, @toasted flaked almonds{25%g}, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and cheese. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer to a deep #ovenproof dish{}. Press down with the back of a #spoon{} so it's level, then set aside.

When the potatoes have ~{25%minutes} left, add the carrot tray to the bottom shelf of your oven and roast for ~{10%minutes}.

After 10 mins, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{200%g} to the same tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then roast until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

At the same time, put the nut roast on the middle shelf to roast for ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Gravy ==

Meanwhile, pop the (now empty) potato pan on medium-high heat.

Melt in the @butter{30%g}, then stir in the @plain flour for the gravy{2%tbsp}. Continue to stir until combined, you've made a roux! Cook, stirring, until the roux is a medium brown colour, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Gradually stir in the @water for the gravy{400%ml}, stir in the @red wine stock paste{56%g}, then bring to the boil, stirring out any lumps that form.

Lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the gravy has thickened to your liking, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, share the nut roast between your plates and serve with the potatoes, carrots and Tenderstem® alongside.

Pour over the gravy to finish.

Enjoy!